{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17656799","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17656799"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:18:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:18:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18763"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18763"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.04,0.09,0.78,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11495"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80368"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11495","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11495"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18763"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65637"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"10188"},{"type":"tags","id":"10201"},{"type":"tags","id":"10203"},{"type":"tags","id":"10207"},{"type":"tags","id":"10213"},{"type":"tags","id":"11317"},{"type":"tags","id":"11383"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26601"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26607"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80368","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80368"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EFollowing a fracture, bone healing progresses through several phases. The final phase involves restoration of normal bone structure and strength.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the remodelling phase of bone healing?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Development of granulation tissue","Recruitment of inflammatory cells","Formation of cartilaginous callus","Replacement of woven bone with lamellar bone","Production of fibrous scar tissue"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe remodelling phase of bone healing involves \u003Cstrong\u003Ereplacement of woven bone with lamellar bone\u003C/strong\u003E. This process occurs through the coordinated action of osteoblasts (which form new bone) and osteoclasts (which remove old bone). The process can take months to years and is influenced by mechanical forces acting on the bone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent earlier phases of bone healing or incorrect processes:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormation of cartilaginous callus\u003C/strong\u003E - This occurs during the soft callus phase, much earlier in the healing process\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDevelopment of granulation tissue\u003C/strong\u003E - This occurs during the inflammatory phase, within the first few days after injury\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecruitment of inflammatory cells\u003C/strong\u003E - This happens immediately after injury during the inflammatory phase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProduction of fibrous scar tissue\u003C/strong\u003E - Bone heals through regeneration rather than scarring\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe remodelling phase results in restoration of normal bone architecture and mechanical strength through the replacement of initially formed woven bone with stronger, more organised lamellar bone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The remodelling phase of bone healing involves coordinated activity of osteoblasts and osteoclasts to restore normal bone architecture.","Remodelling can take months to years to complete and is influenced by mechanical loading.","Woven bone is gradually replaced by stronger lamellar bone during the remodelling phase."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Hall JE, Hall ME. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65637"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18763"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65637","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65637"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T14:46:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T14:46:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11495"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80368"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"h